[normal], adding significantly to pressures in the provider sector
[normal]. As the graph below shows, while 
[normal]‘healthcare’ spending will 
[normal]have 
[normal]increase
[normal]d
[normal] over the period up to 2015/16, once the ITF and transfers to local authorities are accounted for, 
[normal]this translates to
[normal] a 2 per cent real terms cut in ‘NHS’ spending in 2015/16 and a 
[normal]1.4
[normal] per cent
[normal] cut over the period from 2009/10 to 2015/
[normal]16.
