[normal] 
[normal]Boards appear to recognise the need to change gear, with 62 per cent of respondents saying they would like to play a greater role in commissioning services. T
[normal]he requirement that boards sign off local plans will be an important test of their readiness to take on a stronger commissioning role across all services.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]33)
[normal] 
[normal]The long term ambition should be to plan with 100 per cent of NHS and social care resources, not just the 
[normal]3 per cent represented by the 
[normal]ITF
[normal]. 
[normal]This raises bigger 
[normal]questions about 
[normal]whether
[normal] 
[normal]the post-war settlement
[normal],
[normal] which established the NHS as a universal service, free at the point of use and social care as a separately funded, means-tested service
[normal], remains fit for purpose
[normal]. 
[normal]This is why we have
[normal] established an independent commission
[normal],
[normal] chaired by Kate Barker
[normal],
[normal] to explore 
[normal]whether, and if so how, the NHS and social care system should be brought closer together
